<https://www.metaconceptualart.com/data/linked-art/evidence-live-auction-2009> <http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P190_has_symbolic_content> "Sun & Rain Works holds a private archive relating to its March 2009 engagement with Sotheby's Photographs (sale N08533) and the associated conceptual works (The Auction as Artwork, WTF is Ansel Adams, and www.wtfisart.com). The archive is reported to contain 2008 correspondence with Sotheby's, records of the consignment of an Ansel Adams photograph (lot 16), domain-registration and hosting receipts for www.wtfisart.com, photographs, and file metadata. These materials evidence the artist identity, the 2008-2009 engagement with Sotheby's, the consignment, and the website's existence and date. They do not, by themselves, record a publicly witnessed live-creation event, and they establish no precedence over any later event. The fuller archive remains held by the studio pending redaction and rights review; no checksums, file hashes, or custody identifiers are published at this time, and will be added only when the underlying items are released." .
