<https://www.metaconceptualart.com/data/linked-art/priority-live-auction-2009> <http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P129_is_about> <https://www.metaconceptualart.com/data/linked-art/wtfisart> .
<https://www.metaconceptualart.com/data/linked-art/priority-live-auction-2009> <http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P190_has_symbolic_content> "Sun & Rain Works asserts a conceptual claim: that in March 2009, in connection with the Sotheby's Photographs auction (sale N08533, New York), it designated its auction engagement — the consignment of an Ansel Adams photograph, 'San Francisco from Twin Peaks' (lot 16), together with the associated website www.wtfisart.com — as Metaconceptual Art, framed as the work The Auction as Artwork. This is the artist's own designation, made explicit over time. It is not a publicly witnessed live-creation event and has not been adjudicated as a historical fact; the Sotheby's catalogue lists the lot as an Ansel Adams photograph and does not name Sun & Rain Works. This statement makes no claim of being 'first', and does not name, compare against, or dispute any later artist or event; any such comparison would require independent recognition and separately published evidence." .
