_:r17b6 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/E42_Identifier> .
_:r17b7 <http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P190_has_symbolic_content> "A Metaconceptual Art work that Sun & Rain Works designates around its consignment of the Ansel Adams photograph 'San Francisco from Twin Peaks' (lot 16) to Sotheby's Photographs, March 2009 (sale N08533, New York). Titled as a play on the auction and the canonical name of Ansel Adams, it treats the act of bringing the photograph to auction — its lot, its authority, its attribution — as the material of a conceptual work, alongside the born-digital work www.wtfisart.com. The work is a designation asserted by the artist and made explicit over time; it is not recorded as a publicly witnessed performance, and the Sotheby's catalogue lists the lot as an Ansel Adams photograph without naming Sun & Rain Works." .
_:r17b7 <http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P2_has_type> <http://vocab.getty.edu/aat/300435416> .
_:r17b7 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/E33_Linguistic_Object> .
_:r17b8 <http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P190_has_symbolic_content> "Documentation reported by Sun & Rain Works includes 2008 correspondence with Sotheby's Photographs, the public catalogue lot, photographs, and related records; these evidence the artist identity and the consignment. The fuller archive remains held by the studio pending redaction and rights review. This record asserts no historical-priority or precedence claim absent separately published evidence." .
