_:r1b7 <http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P190_has_symbolic_content> "A Metaconceptual Art work that Sun & Rain Works designates in connection with the Sotheby's Photographs auction of March 2009 (sale N08533, New York), at which Sun & Rain Works consigned an Ansel Adams photograph, 'San Francisco from Twin Peaks' (lot 16). Following the logic of the readymade, Sun & Rain Works frames its engagement with that public institutional event — its mechanism of value, authority, and sale — as the material of a conceptual work. This is a designation asserted by the artist and made explicit over time; it is not a publicly witnessed live-creation event, and the Sotheby's catalogue does not name Sun & Rain Works. Two associated works accompany the gesture: the website www.wtfisart.com and WTF is Ansel Adams." .
_:r1b7 <http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P2_has_type> <http://vocab.getty.edu/aat/300435416> .
_:r1b7 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/E33_Linguistic_Object> .
_:r1b8 <http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P190_has_symbolic_content> "Documentation reported by Sun & Rain Works includes 2008 correspondence with Sotheby's Photographs, the public catalogue lot, photographs, receipts, and related records; these evidence the artist identity and the consignment. The fuller archive remains held by the studio pending redaction and rights review. This record makes no adjudicated historical-priority claim and asserts no comparison with, or precedence over, any later artist or event absent separately published evidence." .
_:r1b8 <http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P2_has_type> <http://vocab.getty.edu/aat/300435416> .
